Aldar Rises to 3-Week High in Abu Dhabi After S&P Stable Outlook

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-03-22T06:44:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/aldar-rises-to-3-week-high-in-abu-dhabi-after-s-p-stable-outlook.html
Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR)  rose to the
highest in three weeks as the Abu Dhabi-based developer had its
long-and short-term issuer credit ratings affirmed at B by
 Standard & Poor’s  with a stable outlook.  The shares gained 5.2 percent to 1.43 dirhams, the highest
intraday level since March 1, at 10:38 a.m. in Abu Dhabi
trading. The stock has tumbled 66 percent in the past year.  “The outlook is stable as we expect the government to
continue to support Aldar, enabling it to reach a stable
operational and financial performance over the medium term,”
Standard & Poor’s said in a note yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
